# HTML Page Templates

## Notes Page — Required Skeleton

Every topic notes page (`topic-name.html`) must follow this exact skeleton:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Topic Name — Course Name</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../styles.css" />
  <style>
    /* ── back-link (required on every notes page) ── */
    .back-link {
      display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem;
      font-size: 0.8rem; color: #475569; text-decoration: none;
      margin-bottom: 2rem; transition: color 0.2s;
    }
    .back-link:hover { color: #6366f1; }

    /* page-specific component styles go here */
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">

    <a href="index.html" class="back-link">‹ Course Index Name</a>

    <header class="notes-header">
      <p class="tag">Category · Sub-category</p>
      <h1>Topic Title</h1>
      <p>One-sentence description of what this page covers.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- sections go here -->

    <footer>
      <p>Updated Month Year &nbsp;·&nbsp; lucky &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <a href="index.html" style="color:#475569;text-decoration:none;">← Course Index</a>
      </p>
    </footer>

  </div>
</body>
</html>
```

## Section Pattern — Required for Every Section

Each section of content inside a notes page uses this two-part pattern:

```html
<div class="section-divider"><span>N · Section Title</span><hr /></div>
<div class="card">
  <h2><span class="icon">EMOJI</span> Card Heading</h2>
  <!-- content -->
</div>
```

- Number sections sequentially: `1 ·`, `2 ·`, `3 ·` …
- Every `<div class="section-divider">` is immediately followed by a `<div class="card">`.
- Never put bare text directly inside `.container` — always wrap in a `.card`.

## Course Index Page — Required Skeleton

```html
<header class="notes-header">
  <p class="tag">Course Name</p>
  <h1>Index Title</h1>
  <p>Short description.</p>
</header>

<div class="section-divider"><span>Section Name</span><hr /></div>
<nav class="module-list">

  <a href="topic.html" class="module-card">
    <div class="module-icon">EMOJI</div>
    <div class="module-info">
      <p class="module-tag">Tag1 · Tag2</p>
      <h2>Topic Title</h2>
      <p>One-line description.</p>
    </div>
    <span class="module-arrow">›</span>
  </a>

</nav>
```

## Header Rules

| Context | Class to use |
|---------|-------------|
| Notes page header | `<header class="notes-header">` (indigo left border) |
| Global / course index header | `<header>` (no class) |

- `<p class="tag">` — always the first child of header; uppercase label, indigo color.
- `<h1>` — always the second child; the page title.
- `<p>` — subtitle/description; muted gray.

## Footer — Identical on Every Page

```html
<footer>
  <p>Updated Month Year &nbsp;·&nbsp; lucky &nbsp;·&nbsp;
    <a href="index.html" style="color:#475569;text-decoration:none;">← Index Name</a>
  </p>
</footer>
```

Never omit the footer. Never change its inline style — it intentionally uses `color:#475569`.
